  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: @digininja/postinstall (npm)",
  "details": "The package's postinstall hook runs setup.js, which performs DNS-based exfiltration: it reads the MY_SECRET_API_KEY environment variable and tunnels it via a DNS lookup to a subdomain of the form [apiKey].6u1s7jd9esbax66anvpcg34jgam1asyh[.]collab[.]digi[.]ninja, and also emits a DNS beacon on every install. This is a DNS-tunnelling credential-exfiltration pattern.",
